Answer: <<<api>>>: Activity.findViewById
<<<code>>>: anim_heart = AnimationUtils.loadAnimation(activity, R.anim.heart_anim);
<<<explanation>>>: The error is because you are trying to use the findViewById method from the MainActivity class in the AnimationClass class. This method is used to find views in the layout of the activity, but it is not available in the AnimationClass class. You need to use the findViewById method from the activity that is calling the AnimationClass class.

A: You need to pass the context of the activity to the AnimationClass constructor.
public class AnimationClass {
    private static ImageButton heart_icon,bee_icon;
    private static int kill_flag = 0;
    private static Animation anim_heart, anim_bee;

    public AnimationClass(Context context) {
        heart_icon=(ImageButton)context.findViewById(R.id.heart_icon);
        bee_icon = (ImageButton)context.findViewById(R.id.bee_icon);
    }

    public static void loadAnimations(Activity activity){
        anim_heart = AnimationUtils.loadAnimation(activity, R.anim.heart_anim);
        heart_icon.startAnimation(anim_heart);
        anim_bee = AnimationUtils.loadAnimation(activity, R.anim.bee_anim);
        bee_icon.startAnimation(anim_bee);
    }
}

And then call it like this:
AnimationClass animClass = new AnimationClass(this);
animClass.loadAnimations();
